# <%= packageName %>

This is the <%= description %> AX BI chart plugin.

### Usage

To build the plugin, run the following commands:

```
npm ci
npm run build
```

Alternatively, to run the plugin in development mode (=rebuilding whenever changes are made), start the dev server with the following command:

```
npm run dev
```

To add the package to AX BI, go to the `ax-bi-frontend` subdirectory in your
AX BI source folder (assuming both the `<%= packageName %>` plugin and `ax-bi`
repositories are in the same root directory) and run:
```
npm i -S ../../<%= packageName %>
```

You may also wish to add the following to the `include` array in
`tsconfig.json` to make AX BI types available to your plugin:

```
"../../types/**/*"
```

Finally, if you wish to ensure your plugin `tsconfig.json` is aligned with the
root AX BI project, you may add the following to your `tsconfig.json` file:

```
"extends": "../../tsconfig.json",
```

After this, edit `ax-bi-frontend/src/visualizations/presets/MainPreset.ts` and
make the following changes:

```js
import { <%= packageLabel %> } from '<%= packageName %>';
```

to import the plugin and later add the following to the array that's passed to the `plugins` property:
```js
new <%= packageLabel %>().configure({ key: '<%= packageName %>' }),
```

After that the plugin should show up when you run the AX BI development server:

```
npm run dev-server
```
